value {
  "This display allows monitoring and controlling many parameters useful for normal motor operations."
  "The motor itself is controlled from a dialog screen which is \"popped up\" by pressing the"
  "\"Motor Move\" button in the left bottom corner of this display.  The labels used in this display"
  "are consistent with the terminology used in the Beckhoff manual for the KL2531/KL2541 controllers."
  ""
  "Status Byte is represented as an array of 8 bits."
  "AtTarget, \"Input 2\", and \"Input 1\" are bit 3, 1, and 0 in the  StatWord register;"
  "see Motor Regs/CST screen.  AutoStop is a bit 6 in CtrlByte register; see Morot Regs/CSR."
  "\"Input 1\" and \"Input2\" indicate the state of the limit switches.  When it is bright green,"
  "the limit switch is active."
  ""
  "Reset button is used to clear an Error condition (bit 6 in StatByte).  ClearPosition button"
  "is used to clear the actual position regs. This does not affect the PosFromPot value."
  "Set Position button is used to copy the values from the \"set Position\""
  "registers to the \"actual position\" registers."
  ""
  "\"keep enabled\" toggle button when set causes the motor to remain in enabled state"
  "(holding current on) when a move is completed.  Enable and Start toggle buttons control bits 0"
  "and 2 in CtrlByte register."
  ""
  "Motion Parameters group consists of controls for changing velocity and accelleration values"
  "and Read Back Values (RBV).  \"Steps to Jog\" control is used to enter number of motor steps to"
  "jog the motor position when \"getOffLimit\" button is pressed to move the motor off a limit switch."
  ""
  "\"Actual Position\" area shows the \"actual position\" registers in both number of micro steps as well"
  "as mm wrt to the home position.  Refresh button forces reading these registers."
  "\"Set Position\" shows the \"set position\" registers in units of micro steps and revolutions wrt"
  "the home position.  The control allows changing these registers, where the entered value is in"
  "micro steps.  The Relative position just entered is shown in micro steps."
  "Use the Coeficients button to pop up a dialog which allows changing linear conversion coefficients"
  "for the position values from mm to revolutions and back."
  ""
  "Home:"
  "The Home position is at PosFromPot 0 value; assuming that this has been setup correctly."
  "The correct way to establish the Home position is to drive the motor into the \"left\" limit switch,"
  "step off the limit switch, and click on ClearPosition button in Control screen, and adjust"
  "the potentiometer readout coefficients as needed."
  "If the potentiometer readout is working correctly and it disagrees with PosFromStep value, one"
  "can fix this in the following way:"
  "In \"Move Stage\" dialog for the motor in question, type the value in PosFromPot in setAbsPos"
  "control, press the Enter key, and in Controls dialog press the \"Set Position\" button.  You may"
  "have to Refresh the \"Actual Position\" to verify that all went well.  At this point both"
  "PosFromPot and PosFromStep should show the same values."
  "To force reading the actual position, click on the \"Refresh\" button in this dialog located in"
  "the \"Actual Position\" group."
}
